-- Innodis of Mauritius Rises Most in Month on Dividend Plan
-- B y   K a m l e s h   B h u c k o r y
-- 2012-06-21T10:08:19Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-21/innodis-of-mauritius-rises-most-in-one-month-on-dividend-plan.html
Innodis Ltd. (HWF) , Mauritius’s biggest
food company by market value, climbed the most in more than a
month after announcing a 20 percent increase in its final
dividend for fiscal 2012.  The  shares  climbed 3.1 percent, the most since May 15, to
close at 43.80 rupees in  Port Louis , the capital, the highest
price since May 16.  Innodis will pay a  final dividend  of 0.9 rupee for the
financial year ending June, according to a statement on the
Stock Exchange of Mauritius’s website today. It paid a final
dividend of 0.75 rupee last year, data compiled by Bloomberg
show.  To contact the reporter on this story:
